pageContext.claim: “I leave it up to the governors. The governors know what they're doing. They've been doing a great job. I guess we're close to 90 percent anyway. And the states that we're talking about are not in jeopardy. No, I would leave it to the governors.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump falsely says that the nine states that at the time did not have stay-at-home orders were "not in jeopardy." Any state could quickly become a hotspot for the virus without proper social distancing practices. Three of the states -- Missouri, South Carolina and Utah-- already each had more than 1,000 confirmed cases.
